label.value: high-affinity zinc uptake transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Zn2+(out) -eq- Zn2+(in), probably powered by proton motive force. In high-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations.

label.value: low-affinity zinc ion transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Zn2+ -eq- Zn2+, probably powered by proton motive force. In low-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute only if it is present at very high concentrations.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-6) linkage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  all-trans-hexaprenyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- all-trans-heptaprenyl diphosphate + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within a single-stranded deoxyribonucleic acid molecule by creating internal breaks.
A multimeric enzyme complex, usually a dimer or an octamer, that catalyzes the conversion of 2-phospho-D-glycerate to phosphoenolpyruvate and water.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lactose + H2O -eq- D-glucose + D-galactose.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-2) linkage.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannosyl group to an acceptor molecule, typically another carbohydrate or a lipid.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannosylphosphate group from one compound to another.
Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-3) linkage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenine + H2O -eq- hypoxanthine + NH3.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an acyl group, any group formally derived by removal of the hydroxyl group from the acid function of a carboxylic acid.

label.value: ACP phosphopantetheine attachment site binding involved in fatty acid biosynthetic process

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the attachment site of the phosphopantetheine prosthetic group of an acyl carrier protein (ACP) as part of the process of fatty acid biosynthesis.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidyl-tRNA(1) + aminoacyl-tRNA(2) -eq- tRNA(1) + peptidylaminoacyl-tRNA(2).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with transfer RNA.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with acyl-CoA, any derivative of coenzyme A in which the sulfhydryl group is in thiolester linkage with a fatty acyl group.
Catalysis of the transfer of L-ornithine from one side of a membrane to the other. L-ornithine is 2,5-diaminopentanoic acid.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in G1|S transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any process that regulates transcription such that the target genes are involved in the transition between G1 and S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.
Catalysis of the transfer of S-adenosylmethionine from one side of a membrane to the other. S-adenosylmethionine is S-(5'-adenosyl)-L-methionine, an important intermediate in one-carbon metabolism.

label.value: sulfur amino acid transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of sulfur amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Sulphur amino acids contain sulfur in the form of cystine, methionine or their derivatives.
Catalysis of the transfer of S-methylmethionine from one side of a membrane to the other.

label.value: L-methionine secondary active transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of L-methionine from one side of a membrane to the other, up its concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by a chemiosmotic source of energy. Chemiosmotic sources of energy include uniport, symport or antiport.
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinate + acceptor -eq- fumarate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphoribulosylformimino-AICAR-P + L-glutamine -eq- D-erythro-imidazole-glycerol-phosphate + aminoimidazole carboxamide ribonucleotide + L-glutamate + 2 H(+).
Any complex formed of proteins that act in nucleotide-excision repair.

One of several protein complexes involved in nucleotide-excision repair -  possesses DNA damage recognition and endodeoxynuclease activities. In S. cerevisiae, it is composed of Rad1p, Rad10p, and Rad14p -  in human the subunits are ERCC4|XPF, ERCC1 and XPA, respectively.
